description:
This is my 12th annual Pi Day video. How am I still here? How are you?

I don't usually share "serious" music on the internet but I decided that March 2022 is a time to start. So I'm leaning hard into Pi Day and March 2022 this year, to not let another month slip by in the neverending now.

This piece is dedicated to my patrons, who have supported me with such tremendous faith through many interesting times. The 45 minute piano masterclass on this piece is now available here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-4Zt5HxSCbo

Shiny Merch? yep, it is here: https://store.dftba.com/collections/vi-hart

You can buy the sheetmusic and recording for the Pi Day 2022 piano composition here: https://store.dftba.com/products/piano-sheet-music-digital-download-and-mp3 

Exclusive shirt, cryptic edition, doubles as a puzzle: https://store.dftba.com/products/pi-day-2022-exclusive-shirt-cryptic-edition
Exclusive shirt, shiny edition, is special and shiny: https://store.dftba.com/products/pi-day-2022-exclusive-shirt-shiny-edition

Triangle Pins! https://store.dftba.com/collections/vi-hart/products/triangle-pin

And finally, the challenge coin and 314 digits of pi sheetmusic, available in many clefs as well as guitar tabs: https://store.dftba.com/products/pi-chromatic-challenge-metal-coin-and-digital-download

I will see you again soon. The best place to stay updated is probably on Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/vihart

Extra shoutout to Caleb Wright and Ray Sidney, who have been staunch supporters of my piano, as well as Pat Devlin, David Perryman, Andew Romaner, Andrea Bi Biagio, Jodi Vezzetti, Yana Chernobilsky, David Smith, Alan Boulton, and Nancy Blachman!
